Niger State has recorded its first coronavirus death after the National Center for Disease Control (NCDC) confirmed eight new cases in the State. Making the revelation in Minna, the State Commissioner for Health and Hospital Services Dr. Muhammad Makusidi stated that out of the 22 results received from the NCDC, eight persons have tested positive to the disease while 14 returned negative. He noted that out of the eight positive cases confirmed, seven are Almajiri returnees from Zaria, Kaduna State. According to him, the deceased aged 40 years, was a taxi driver plying the Suleja- Abuja route. ” The deceased who is 40 years of age was diabetic. He died shortly on arrival at the Suleja- General Hospital. ” A postmortem sample was taken for test and it returned positive, while contact tracing will commence with immediate effect.” Niger State has currently a total of 22 confirmed cases as at 16th of May 2020 with one mortality. Niger State government confirms four new cases says patients in stable condition Nigerian Newspapers: 10 things you need to know this Monday Morning Ekiti govt confirms 3 new cases of coronavirus These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More